FinancialInstitution 1 -- * ReusableFinancialInstrument
A ReusableFinancialInstrument has A FinancialInstitution. It must always have exactly, one, and can never have none. And there is an upper bound of at most one FinancialInstitution.
A FinancialInstitution has some ReusableFinancialInstruments. It can have none, and there is no upper bound defined.
When a ReusableFinancialInstrument is created, its FinancialInstitution must be assigned. When a ReusableFinancialInstrument is deleted, its FinancialInstitution is not deleted and its list of ReusableFinancialInstruments is decreased. When a FinancialInstitution is deleted, its ReusableFinancialInstruments are not deleted. They are assigned to another FinancialInstitution.
